Systemic review published in Gynecological Endocrinology 2009 suggested benefit of D-chiro-Inositol in improving PCOS parameters
NOT A CLINICAL STUDY- ONLY HYPOTHESIS. Undid revision 766876956 by [[Special:Contributions/Petergstrom|Petergstrom]] ([[User talk:Petergstrom|talk]])

Recent clinical trial published in Gynecological Endocrinology in 2014 showed that D-chiro-Inositol is effective in restoring better insulin sensitivity and an improving hormonal pattern in obese hyperinsulinemic PCOS patients.

Recent clinical trial published in August 2016, showed that D-chiro-Inositol significantly improved menstrual regularity, Acne Score, endocrine and metabolic parameters and insulin-resistence in young, overweight, PCOS patients.
Research published in The New England Journal of Medicine having impact factor of  59.558 (the highest among general medical journals) showing that D-chiro-Inositol is effective in treatment of PCOS.
Recent evidence showing role of D chiro inositol in improving symtoms of Polycystic ovarian syndrome
